<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Communications Coordinator</a></h2>
<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Communications Coordinator<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Executive Director<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, 12 months, salaried monthly, exempt status
</p>

<p>Develops and produces materials pertaining to education and children with disabilities and public information about PACER Center.</p>
<h3>RESPONSIBILITIES</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Editorial
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Writes, edits, designs, provides desktop for PACESETTER newsletter &ndash; three times per year. Involves researching, developing, and writing clear, accurate, concise hard news and feature articles. Must have interest in and sensitivity to in-depth interviews involving human experiences, as well as complex legislative and public policy issues. Must have experience and knowledge of publication production from concept through print.</li>
			<li>Reviews, edits, written materials, including other newsletters, produced by other staff. Must know and adhere to prescribed editing style, preferably AP or Chicago Manual of Style. Must be able to explain publication production so that others understand process and deadlines.</li>
			<li>Offers guidance writing, editing, publications process, and production as requested.</li>
			<li>Makes assignments to and supervises other staff.</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
	<li style="padding-top: .5em;">Media relations
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Initiates media coverage of issues and events related to PACER&rsquo;s work, ranging from high-profile public events and sensitive legislative issues to regularly scheduled workshops. Must have working knowledge of media ethics and expectations.</li>
			<li>Responds to incoming media requests. Must understand PACER policy, plus how media operates&nbsp; to facilitate requests</li>
			<li>Oversees PACER&#8217;s media list.</li>
			<li>Tracks media coverage, maintains archives.</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
	<li style="padding-top: .5em;">Videos
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Develops and writes scripts</li>
			<li>Acts as producer for PACER Center videos, including coordinating shoots, locating &lsquo;actors,&rsquo; developing production schedule, assisting videographer at on- and off-site shoots. Requires organizational skills, flexibility, stamina, and willingness to work outside the regular work day</li>
			<li>Arranges for product copies dissemination</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
	<li style="padding-top: .5em;">Photography
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Takes photos for publications, of events, and upon request. Must understand concepts of photography and components of compelling composition</li>
			<li>Downloads digital photos or arranges for processing of photos</li>
			<li>Catalogs photos, maintains archives</li>
			<li>Catalogs photographic permissions</li>
			<li>Works with executive assistant to provide photos for miscellaneous PACER project requests</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
	<li style="padding-top: .5em;">Benefit
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Works with volunteer publicity chair to provide media relations, promotions. Includes coordinating media contacts, developing interviews, producing press releases, tracking responses. Is in-house media contact. See requirements for media relations.</li>
			<li>Provides and reviews printed Benefit materials as requested. </li>
			<li>Writes and produces Benefit video</li>
			<li>Takes photos, assigns and supervises other photographers on Benefit night</li>
			<li>Oversees processing of photographic gift prints</li>
			<li>Other Benefit coordination as may be assigned</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
	<li style="padding-top: .5em;">Other duties as may be assigned
		<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
			<li>Participates in special events, fundraising</li>
			<li>Coordinates events upon request</li>
			<li>Other</li>
		</ol>
	</li>
</ol>

<h3>Requirements for position:</h3>
<ol>
<li>College degree, preferably in journalism, communications, or related field</li>
<li>Excellent writing and editing skills</li>
<li>Five or more years in publications interviewing, writing, editing, design and print production</li>
<li>Ability to research and synthesize information, then reproduce succinct copy for written materials</li>
<li>Working knowledge of copyright, privacy, libel and other publications-related legal issues</li>
<li>Demonstrated creativity</li>
<li>Attention to detail and deadlines</li>
<li>Sensitivity and interpersonal skills that encourage teamwork</li>
<li>Ability to communicate with people from diverse backgrounds</li>
<li>Knowledge of public education; governmental systems; and how policy is made</li>
</ol>

<p>
Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.
</p>
<p>
<strong>SALARY</strong>: To be determined based on experience.<br />
Position available immediately.
</p>

